Results: gmd:dataQualityInfo.gmd:DQ_DataQuality.gmd:lineage.gmd:LI_Lineage.gmd:statement.gco:CharacterString.#text:§The DTS unit was configured in double-ended configuration to collect data at 25 cm and 10 minutes sampling interval. Two calibration baths (one at the ambient temperature and a fridge), as well as PT100 probes (0.1°C) and RBR SoloT probes (0.002°C accuracy) were used to calibrate the data. To assess the accuracy of temperature measurements, a RBR SoloT probe was set up at the gauging station E30 located at the entrance of the wood (shed).
Valeurs: The DTS unit was configured in double-ended configuration to collect data at 25 cm and 10 minutes sampling interval. Two calibration baths (one at the ambient temperature and a fridge), as well as PT100 probes (0.1°C) and RBR SoloT probes (0.002°C accuracy) were used to calibrate the data. To assess the accuracy of temperature measurements, a RBR SoloT probe was set up at the gauging station E30 located at the entrance of the wood (shed).
